transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Customs and Sheriffs, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I placed an order with Fort Blue.

Speaker 1: I thought I was getting a new Viagra, but I'm not sure it would be something.

Speaker 2: Well, they sent me just the same little Centafil that I've been taking,

Speaker 1: but I got from other doctors, my regular doctor, and it doesn't even work.

Speaker 2: What's your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: Richard Crosby, June 10, 1958.

Speaker 2: It's supposed to have been the Viagra AGV is what I ordered.

Speaker 1: Okay. Are you still on Jerry Jones?

Speaker 2: Yes, ma'am, I am.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm going to set up the Centafil for the AGV.

Speaker 2: Give me a second.

Speaker 1: Okay, this will go out today.

Speaker 2: Oh, they're going to send me the other one?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's going to go out today.

Speaker 2: Will it cost me any extra?

Speaker 1: No, I didn't charge you.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good day. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye-bye.
